**Net income per common share (2008)**  

- **Basic EPS**  
  \[
  \text{Basic EPS} = \frac{\text{Net income available for common shareholders}}{\text{Weighted‑average common shares outstanding}}
  = \frac{56{,}616}{146{,}915}\approx 0.385\;\text{dollars per share}
  \]

  Rounded to two decimal places, **basic net income per common share ≈ $0.39**.

- **Diluted EPS** (for completeness)  
  \[
  \text{Diluted EPS} = \frac{\text{Diluted net income available for common shareholders}}{\text{Weighted‑average common shares + potential dilutive securities}}
  = \frac{59{,}584}{155{,}041}\approx 0.385\;\text{dollars per share}
  \]

Thus, the net income per common share in 2008 is about **$0.39 per share** (basic EPS).
